     <p class="B3BodyText">In Derry, the four grammar  schools educate 43% of post-primary pupils in the county; the other nine non-grammar  schools educate the remaining 57%, and 13% of children are entitled to free  school meals. From the three primary schools largely serving the Sandy Row  area, 11 out of 79 pupils transferred to a grammar school. From the three  primary schools largely serving the Shankill area, 10 transferred to a grammar  school; and from the seven primary schools serving the Falls Road 49 out of 284  children transferred to a grammar school. We need to get real if we intend to  bring about change.</p>
